<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HACKETT HEADACHE: BIG RIVALS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ It's been a fairly satisfying year for USC so far,
but coach Paul Hackett knows that the success of his inaugural
season will probably be determined by how the Trojans fare in their
final two games, against archrivals UCLA and Notre Dame.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is going to be the true judge of the season. Let's face
it, if we lose our last two games, everyone will say, `How did they
do? Well, they went 7-5,''' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   On Tuesday, Hackett was perplexed over USC's seven-year losing
streak to the Bruins.
</P>
<P>
   ``Nothing's more important than beating UCLA. It's still
incomprehensible to me that we lost seven straight years,'' Hackett
said. ``Maybe I'll see clearer after the game.''
</P>
<P>
   The last time USC defeated UCLA and Notre Dame in the same year
was in 1981, and those weren't back-to-back games. The last USC
team to sweep both schools on consecutive weekends did it in 1978.
</P>
<P>
   ``Are we there yet? I don't know yet,'' Hackett said. ``Can we
beat them on back-to-back weekends? That's tall stuff. We have to
be ready to go.''
</P>
<P>
   Will R. Jay play? Wide receiver R. Jay Soward wore a boot on his
sprained right ankle Tuesday, as his status for the UCLA game
remains in doubt.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's never been hurt,'' Hackett said. ``I don't know how we
can predict anything. Obviously, we'll be super-super cautious this
week. Maybe in the middle of next week, we'll know more.
</P>
<P>
   ``A guy like that never gets hurt. It hasn't happened before.
This is very hard. There's nothing you can do about this. We know
how great he's played against UCLA.''
</P>
<P>
   Soward declined comment Tuesday when asked by reporters about
his ankle.
</P>
<P>
   Another commitment: USC has received an oral commitment from
Long Beach Poly wide receiver Kareem Kelly, who is rated as an
All-American by most recruiting services.
</P>
<P>
   Kelly's teammate, All-American cornerback Darrell Rideaux,
currently favors USC over Notre Dame.
</P>
<P>
   Bastianelli hurt: Wide receiver Mike Bastianelli suffered a
sprained medial collateral ligament in his knee against Stanford
and will be forced to wear a brace for the final two games.
</P>
<P>
   It is not expected to cause him to miss any games.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
