</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Was that R.E.M. or Run-DMC?
 &HT;    (EDS: Can run with EIGHTIES-NOSTALGIA)
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are some lyrics from ``Who Can It Be Now?'' Try to identify
the artist and the song. Answers are given at right.
</P>
<P>
   _ 1. ``You take me by the heart when you take me by the hand.''
</P>
<P>
   _ 2. ``He just smiled and gave me a Vegemite sandwich.''
</P>
<P>
   _ 3. ``You make the sun shine brighter than Doris Day.''
</P>
<P>
   _ 4. ``Your heart sweats, your body shakes.''
</P>
<P>
   _ 5. ``Straddle the line in discord and rhyme.''
</P>
<P>
   _ 6. ``Lenny Bruce is not afraid.''
</P>
<P>
   _ 7. ``You don't have to watch `Dynasty' to have an attitude.''
</P>
<P>
   _ 8. ``Tommy used to work on the docks.''
</P>
<P>
   _ 9. ``To rock a rhyme that's right on time.''
</P>
<P>
   _ 10. ``Why do I find it hard to write the next line?''
</P>
<P>
   ANSWERS
</P>
<P>
   1. Toni Basil, ``Mickey'' 2. Men at Work, ``Down Under'' 3.
Wham! ``Wake Me Up Before You Go Go'' 4. Robert Palmer, ``Addicted
to Love'' 5. Duran Duran, ``Hungry Like the Wolf'' 6. R.E.M.,
``It's the End of the World as We Know It (And I Feel Fine)'' 7.
Prince, ``Kiss'' 8. Bon Jovi, ``Living on a Prayer'' 9. Run-DMC,
``It's Tricky'' 10. Spandau Ballet, ``True.''
</P>
