</P>
<P>
   Doctors Without Borders has programs in Nicaragua, Honduras and
Guatemala, and is monitoring the situation in Costa Rica, El
Salvador, Belize and Mexico. Donations to the Hurricane Mitch
Relief Effort can be made to: Doctors Without Borders, 6 E. 39th
St., 8th Floor, New York, NY 10016. Information: 1-888-392-0392.
</P>
<P>
   The American Red Cross also is supporting Central American
relief efforts. Checks or money orders can be sent to: American Red
Cross International Response Fund, P.O. Box 37243, Washington, DC
20013. For a credit card donation, call 1-800-435-7669 or
1-800-257-7575 (Spanish). Internet users can make an online credit
card donation at http://www.redcross.org and choosing International
Relief Fund as their option of giving.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I remember that back in the '80s, Roanoke, Va., had a female
symphony conductor who was up-and-coming and making a reputation
