<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    ECONOMIC DATA ON THE 21 APEC PARTNERS
 &HT;    With ASIA-SUMMIT-$ADV15, CLINTON-ASIA-$ADV15.
 &HT;    EDs: Suitable to run with map of countries.
 &HT;    For Use Sun., Nov. 15 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The 21-nation Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation
forum will meet from Nov. 17-18 in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia to
discuss major trade issues. But what will be foremost on the minds
of many is how to bring the region -- and Russia -- out of a the
malaise that it has been in for 17 months, and is threatening the
global economy.
</P>
<P>
   Following are thumbnail economic profiles of all of the
countries:
</P>
<P>
   UNITED STATES
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 3.5 million sq. mi.; Capital, Washington, D.C.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 266.5 million
</P>
<P>
   Government: Democratic republic
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $7.576 trillion (1996)
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, $855.2 billion; Imports, $953.9 billion (1996)
</P>
<P>
   Currency: American dollar
</P>
<P>
   AUSTRALIA
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 3 million sq. mi., about the size of the 48
continental U.S.; Capital, Canberra.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 18.7 million
</P>
<P>
   Government: Democratic, federal-state system recognizing British
monarch as sovereign.
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP $350 billion
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, $56 billion (1997); Imports, $59 billion (1998)
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Australian dollar.
</P>
<P>
   BRUNEI DARUSSALAM
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 2,227 sq. mi., slightly larger than Delaware;
Capital, Bandar Seri Begawan.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 320,000 (1998)
</P>
<P>
   Government: Sultanate
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $4.9 billion (1997).
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, N/A; Imports, N/A.
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Brunei dollar
</P>
<P>
   CANADA
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 3.8 million sq. mi, second largest country in
the world; Capital, Ottawa.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 30.2 million.
</P>
<P>
   Government: Confederation, with parliamentary democracy.
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $585.1 billion (1996)
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Merchandise Exports, $196.21 billion; Merchandise
Imports, $170.9 billion (1996)
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Canadian dollar.
</P>
<P>
   CHILE
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 302,778 sq. mi., nearly twice the size of
California.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 14.6 million (1997)
</P>
<P>
   Government: Republic
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $77.1 billion (1997)
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, $15.4 billion; Imports, $17.4 billion (1996).
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Peso
</P>
<P>
   CHINA
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 3.7 million sq. mi.; Capital, Beijing.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 1.22 billion (1997)
</P>
<P>
   Government: Communist Party-led state.
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $890 billion (1997, exchange rate-based).
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, $182.7 billion; Imports, $142.36 billion (1997).
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Yuan
</P>
<P>
   HONG KONG (Special Administrative Region)
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 1,092 sq. km.; Hong Kong comprises Hong Kong
Island, Kowloon, the New Territories and numerous small islands.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 6.7 million (1998)
</P>
<P>
   Government: Special Administrative Region of China, with its own
constitution (Basic Law).
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $172 billion (1997).
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, $188 billion; Imports, $209 billion (1997).
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Hong Kong dollar
</P>
<P>
   INDONESIA
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 736,000 sq. mi, about three times the size of
Texas; maritime area, 7.9 million sq. km.; Capital, Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 201 million (1997)
</P>
<P>
   Government: Independent republic.
</P>
<P>
   Economy: $211 billion (1997); $90 billion (est. 1998).
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, $56.3 billion (1997), $12.5 billion (est. 1998);
Imports, $46.2 billion (1997), $7.2 billion (est. 1998).
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Rupiah
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 145,856 sq. mi., slightly smaller than
California; Capital, Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 126 million (1997).
</P>
<P>
   Government: Constitutional monarchy, with a parliamentary
government.
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $2.85 trillion (1997).
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, $411 billion; Imports, $329 billion (1997)
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Yen
</P>
<P>
   MALAYSIA
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 127,316 sq. mi., slightly larger than New
Mexico; Capital, Kuala Lumpur.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 21.7 million (1997).
</P>
<P>
   Government: Federal parliamentary democracy, with a
constitutional monarch.
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $93.6 billion (1997)
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, $79 billion; Imports, $79 billion (1997).
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Ringgit
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 761,000 sq. mi., about three times the size of
Texas; Capital, Mexico City.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 95 million (est. 1997).
</P>
<P>
   Government: Federal republic
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $415 billion (1997).
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Merchandise Exports, $110.3 billion; Merchandise Imports,
$109.8 billion (1997).
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Peso
</P>
<P>
   NEW ZEALAND
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 104,440 sq. mi., about the size of Colorado;
Capital, Wellington.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 3.7 million (est. 1997).
</P>
<P>
   Government: Parliamentary
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $64.4 billion (1997).
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, $12 billion; Imports, $21.3 billion (1996).
</P>
<P>
   Currency: New Zealand dollar
</P>
<P>
   PAPUA NEW GUINEA
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 452,860 sq. km., about the size of California;
Capital, Port Moresby.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 4.5 million
</P>
<P>
   Government: Constitutional monarchy, with parliamentary
democracy.
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $4.655 billion (1997)
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, $2.2 billion; Imports, $1.5 billion (1997)
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Kina
</P>
<P>
   PERU
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 496,225 sq. mi., three times larger than
California; Capital, Lima.
</P>
<P>
   Population: 24.9 million (est. 1997)
</P>
<P>
   Government: Constitutional republic.
</P>
<P>
   Economy: GDP, $54.0 billion (est. 1997)
</P>
<P>
   Trade: Exports, $6.8 billion; Imports, $8.6 billion (est. 1997).
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Sol
</P>
<P>
   THE PHILIPPINES
</P>
<P>
   Geography: Area, 117,187 sq. mi.; Capital, Manila.
