<HEADLINE>
CLINTON'S INTERNET ENVOY TO RESIGN 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 By JERI CLAUSING   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
 &HT;    
 &HT;    WASHINGTON _ Ira Magaziner, the author of the Clinton
administration's ill-fated national health plan, who most recently
has led government efforts to foster the growth of the Internet and
electronic commerce, said Friday that he would leave the White
House before the end of the year. U,F,: - BC-TECH-REPORT10-COX, -  
 BC-TECH-REPORT10-COX 
 &HT;    
 &HT;    Titantic CD-ROM offers unreleased film footage
 &HT;    By Mark Clothier
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ If you're one of the millions who didn't see
``Titanic,'' the movie and didn't buy the video, the soundtrack or
the book, there's still at least one more chance to give money to
James Cameron this year.
</P>
<P>
   Fox Interactive is releasing James Cameron's Titanic Explorer, a
CD-ROM, at a suggested $35. It is billed as the only Titanic
multimedia product that blends a historical database with
previously unreleased film footage. Users will be able to tour the
ship and see what it looked like on its maiden voyage. U,F,9 -
BC-TECHNOBUDDY10-COX, -  &QL; 
 &UR; BC-TECHNOBUDDY10-COX &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Ham radio brings out the adolescent squeal in me
</P>
<P>
   By Bill Husted
</P>
<P>
   c. 1998 Cox News Service
</P>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ For the first time in nearly two years, I hooked my
ham radio station up to an antenna and _ in just seconds _ I was 13
years old again. U,F,: - BC-TECHTOOLS10-COX, -  &QL; 
