 By STEVE LOHR   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   As its antitrust trial moves into the fourth week, Microsoft
Corp. finds itself trying to deflect a flood of charges of threats
and bribes. The litany of shameful misconduct, according to the
government, was directed not only at Microsoft's rivals but just
about everyone in the industry _ including personal computer
makers, Internet service suppliers and others. nn
