<HEADER>
A5616 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BRANDY-MUSIC-LADN     11-11 1186
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BRANDY-MUSIC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BRANDY POURS IT ON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED SHUSTER 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ You won't confuse the Brandy Norwood of ``Moesha''
and ``Cinderella'' with the part the teen r&AMP;b queen plays in the
slasher sequel ``I Still Know What You Did Last Summer.''
</P>
<P>
   In the film, which opens Friday and also features Jennifer Love
Hewitt of TV's ``Party of Five,'' Brandy's tough-talking character,
Karla, makes out with co-star Mekhi Phifer in a hot tub, runs
around the Bahamas in a skimpy bathing suit and kickboxes the
movie's murderous fisherman.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm so bad in this, saying bad words and stuff,'' admits
Brandy, who lives in Woodland Hills and recently scored a No. 1 pop
smash with ``The Boy Is Mine,'' a duet with fellow single-named r&AMP;b
sensation, Monica. ``My mom was at the screening, and I kept
saying, `Mom, it's in the script. I had to say it'.''
</P>
<P>
   The new fright flick, which follows last year's teen horror
smash, ``I Know What You Did Last Summer,'' was shot mostly over a
month's time in various remote locations in Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   It was the first feature film for 19-year-old Brandy, who
co-starred last year with Whitney Houston and Whoopi Goldberg in a
highly rated TV-film version of Rodgers &AMP; Hammerstein's
``Cinderella.'' The singer says she was none too pleased with
Mexico's 90-degree-plus tropical climate _ not to mention the
creepy, crawly things that invaded the set.
</P>
<P>
   ``We were there for a month _ and that was a month too long,''
Brandy said. ``I wanted to go back home in three days. I wasn't
used to these animals _ lemurs and geckos and scorpions and things.
One of the actresses woke up with a crab on her head. But I brought
Raid. I hated it.''
</P>
<P>
   On the set, Brandy hit it off with Hewitt, who also sings, stars
in a hit TV series and again plays Julie James in ``I Still Know
... .'' Brandy's ``Moesha,'' currently in its fourth season, is the
UPN network's highest-rated series.
</P>
<P>
   Hewitt, who has done eight films, said the camaraderie that
developed in Mexico is apparent on screen.
</P>
<P>
   ``This movie couldn't be done without every actor pulling their
weight, whether they acted in a film before or not,'' she said.
``It was a tough shoot being in the rain and being in Mexico, but
everyone was so brave and great.''
</P>
<P>
   In ``I Still Know ...,'' Brandy's Karla Wilson character is
Julie's best friend and roommate but knows nothing about Julie's
paranoia and fear of the fisherman, Ben Willis (Muse Watson).
</P>
<P>
   The girls win an all-expense-paid Bahamas vacation for four
during the July 4 weekend. Karla's main squeeze, Tyrell Martin
(Phifer) and Julie's classmate Will Benson (Matthew Settle) are
invited to tag along. Upon their arrival, other guests begin
leaving, a terrible storm moves in, and a series of brutal murders
begin.
</P>
<P>
   ``Karla was the type of person I'd hang out with,'' Brandy said.
``She's someone I'd feel safe with. She could tell people what to
do, and she was hard and a kickboxer. I loved it. I want to do more
challenging roles like that. Moesha is so next-door. The baddest
thing she's ever done is sneak out a window to see a guy, and
that's not so bad. Then you have Cinderella who's so perfect. I
need to do something different.''
</P>
<P>
   Director Danny Cannon said Brandy fell into her Karla role
surprisingly easily.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it was a lot more physical and exhausting than she
thought it would be,'' he said. ``I allowed her to put a lot of
herself into the part, to use her own instincts. She learned very
quickly, and she's a great girl. She was a trouper.''
</P>
<P>
   In fact, Brandy will team with Diana Ross as mother and daughter
in the ABC-TV drama ``Double Platinum,'' which begins shooting next
month in New York for May sweeps. The film is being produced by
Brandy's Norwood Ent. Group.
</P>
<P>
   Fans of Brandy's singing are apparently willing to accept the
singer as a dramatic actor.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't call her a singer or an actor,'' said Vivian Matthew
Yarde, a 20-year-old freshman at the University of the Virgin
Islands who runs a Web site devoted to all things Brandy. ``I think
of her as a professional entertainer.''
</P>
<P>
   For her part, Brandy said she believes fans of such
multimillion-selling albums as her current ``Never Say Never''
(Atlantic) realize she must accept different parts to grow as an
actor.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think they'll be upset (by Karla's behavior),'' Brandy
said. ``I want to be an entertainer, period. I want to do
everything: movies, TV, modeling, commercials. But that's the
downside of fame _ you have to always live up to expectations, to
what people think you are. I am a lot of the way people think I am,
but then again, I'm human.''
</P>
<P>
   Brandy said one of her trickiest scenes in ``I Still Know What
You Did Last Summer'' required her to kiss co-star Phifer.
</P>
<P>
   ``I said, `Mekhi, now, I haven't kissed that many guys, so I
don't know if I'll be any good,' '' Brandy recalled. ``He said,
`Brandy, just do it.' We developed a relationship outside the movie
where we'd always hang out, his cousin, my friends. We had a
wonderful time together.''
</P>
<P>
   Is Brandy's real-life personality similar to that of the
tough-talking Karla? Or is she more like girl-next-door Moesha?
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm tough and I'm sweet, but if you mess with me I'll go crazy
on you, and that's the way I am,'' she declared.
</P>
<P>
   As for whether she prefers singing or acting, Brandy chose
acting because ``it's more of a challenge since I have to always
please somebody else. I like that. I like the fact I have to
challenge myself to do a good job.''
</P>
<P>
   Brandy hit back at reports that she and duet partner Monica
fought at rehearsals for the recent MTV Video Music Awards at the
Universal Amphitheatre.
</P>
<P>
   ``I can't kill a fly,'' she said. ``I know it looks like that in
the movies, but I can't hit. I'm not punching other people. If
anything, they're punching me. No, the truth is, I'm cool with her.
It's hard to call someone a friend right off the bat. But I respect
her. I love her music. I love what she's done, her image and
everything. That's why I chose her to be on my song.''
</P>
<P>
   As for her goals, Brandy said she doesn't want to have to work
if she doesn't want to by the time she reaches the ripe old age of
23.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not going to retire,'' she explained. ``I just don't want
to have to work. I'll be like Julia Roberts _ I'll just do movies
for the heck of it. Some of these people doing movies are doing it
only because they love the work. That's what I want to do.''
</P>
<P>
   Another goal involves making a film with comic actor Chris
Tucker of ``Rush Hour'' fame.
</P>
<P>
   ``First, I want to do a movie where I'm the killer, then I want
to do a romantic comedy with Chris, because he can just make me
laugh and make me a better actress,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Brandy says she has two close friends in Woodland Hills who
treat her as a normal person, not a star.
</P>
<P>
   ``We just love each other to death,'' she said. ``They don't
care who I am, and they don't treat me like a celebrity. My friends
support me, but they tell me the truth.''
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
