<P>
   TECH-MUSEUM _ SAN JOSE, Calif. _ The Tech Museum, the new $96
million interactive monument to Silicon Valley, doesn't feel like a
museum. The 132,000-square-foot museum in downtown San Jose is less
a record of what Silicon Valley has achieved than a living
laboratory where mind-bending exhibits illustrate how today's
technology works and where it's headed. (Hawkins, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SMALLBIZ-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ According to Tom Fornoff, vice
president of corporate marketing of IntelliQuest Inc., the number
of people on the Web is expected to continue to grow, reaching 110
million users in another two years. Those buying online are now
spending an average of $100 a month, but that will more than double
in three years, predicts Fornoff. (Tyson, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
