   FBC-UGA-AUBURN _ The Georgia defense has come under fire in
recent weeks, struggling to hold off Kentucky before falling flat
in a 38-7 loss to Florida. The Bulldogs hope to regain their touch
Saturday against Auburn, which has struggled on offense this season
while looking to replace quarterback Dameyune Craig. But the Tigers
have a recent history of success against the Georgia defense,
scoring 94 points in their last two games. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
