   FBC-BOHLS-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ If you haven't noticed _ and
those solar eclipses are a good sign _ the pattern of supersized
football players has filtered down to the college level. In the Big
12 alone, team rosters include 118 players who weigh at least 300
pounds, 15 of them true freshmen. Thank God for wide-angle lenses.
(Bohls, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WTL-WEIGHTS _ Robin Byrd Goad, who won three medals Tuesday in
the World Weightlifting Championships in Lahti, Finland, has been
lifting on a world level since 1987. But now she has new
motivation: Women's weightlifting will be an Olympic sport for the
first time in 2000. (Rosen, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TEX-HUNTINGSEASON _ SPICEWOOD, Texas _ Griff Andrews is building
the mother of all campfires _ a hair-singeing, boot-melting eternal
flame _ to ward off the nasty wet chill that has settled on Red
Bluff Ranch. Deer season has begun in Texas, and with it the
culture of hunting (Leggett, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
