<P>
   GROCERY BARGAINS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ I'm cheap and I'm proud of it. It's not how
much money you earn, it's how much you save. And, honey, I'm a
champ. But my biggest secret for saving money? Town Talk. Despite
the fact that Town Talk has been around in one form or another for
more than 40 years, it's barely a blip on most shoppers' radar
screens. But for those who live for bargains, this cement-floored
metal building in east Fort Worth is the Valhalla of value. Nowhere
else can you find cans of artichoke hearts for 99 cents, 5-pound
bags of frozen hash-browned potatoes for $1.50 and frozen yellowfin
tuna for $3 a pound. By BEVERY BUNDY. Story has moved in ``d'' food
and dining category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
