   UNDATED _ If his detractors were thinking that they'd heard the
last of Newt Gingrich, they'd better think again. The
soon-to-retire U.S. House speaker showed up on television Monday
night, reminding some of his most devoted followers that his
decision to surrender the congressional gavel should not be
interpreted as an all-out retreat from public life. By BILL
THOMPSON. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
