<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUSINESS-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Thursday, Nov. 12, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-JOBS (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles County's
entertainment industry has slowed dramatically this year with job
growth at its lowest level since the 1992 recession, a forecaster
said Wednesday. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   MARY-FOREIGN (Los Angeles) _ ``There's Something About Mary,''
underscoring the pervasive influence of American culture in
overseas markets, is becoming a major hit in foreign theaters
despite its gross-out humor. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   SKUNK-JOBS (Lancaster, Calif.) _ Lockheed Martin Skunk Works
Executive Vice President Paul Martin said the company could gain
8,000 jobs if Lockheed Martin wins the Joint Strike Fighter
contract for which it is competing with Boeing. By Jim Skeen.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
