<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, NOVEMBER 12
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-COMPAQ-STRATEGY-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Nov. 10)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Nov. 10,
about Compaq Computer's plan to sell directly to consumers
misspelled the given name of the president of Tech Data, a computer
wholesaler that could be affected. He is Anthony A. Ibarguen, not
Antony.
</P>
<P>
   BC-REALITY-MAGS-MEDIA-NYT (moved on Sunday, Nov. 8)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Nov. 8,
about realistic themes in glossy consumer magazines misspelled the
surname of the designer of sequins worn by a model in More
magazine. He is Carmen Marc Valvo, not Valco. The article misstated
the title of Charles A. Riley 2d at We magazine. He is the editor
in chief, not the publisher.
</P>
