<SLUG> BC-PEACHBUZZ1112-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Peach Buzz
 &HT;    By Richard L. Eldredge
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Vets remembered
</P>
<P>
   Thanks to Berkmar High School principal Jim Markham, Veteran's
Day in Gwinnett County, Ga., did not go unrecognized. The Vietnam
vet contacted about 75 local churches with bells and requested that
the bells ring for one full minute at noon.
</P>
<P>
   He enlisted musically inclined residents to pick up a horn at 6
p.m. Wednesday and blow taps throughout the county. Even more
amazing is that Markham managed to organize all this while battling
bone cancer.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just wanted a reflective moment for those who gave their
lives in America's wars,'' explains Markham. ``It's my good fortune
to be responsible for organizing these activities.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
