CALIFORNIAN WON'T ENTER MAJORITY LEADER RACE
</HEADLINE>
   (htv) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Rep. Bill Thomas, R-Calif., has decided not to
enter the race for House majority leader, the No. 2 leadership
position, leaving three candidates to battle it out.
</P>
<P>
   Aides to Thomas said he would support Rep. Dick Armey of Texas,
