<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDINALS-CENTERS-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AT LONG LAST, A BIG GAME  
 CENTERS WAITED 9 YEARS FOR SUNDAY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Cardinals fullback Larry Centers has waited nine years for a
game as big as Sunday's.
</P>
<P>
   The (John) Madden cruiser looking for a parking spot. Hall of
Famer Terry Bradshaw showing up at a practice. A fan from Minsk,
Belarus (of the former Soviet Union), inquiring about buying team
merchandise. Businesses offering to feed the players breakfast the
rest of the week in helping them try to ``Destroy Dallas.''
</P>
<P>
   There's more coming. Red pompons will be passed to a sold-out
crowd when it enters Sun Devil Stadium Sunday for the game between
the Cardinals (5-4) and the NFC East-leading Dallas Cowboys (6-3).
</P>
<P>
   Centers isn't complaining about the distractions, not when he's
had so many meaningless games in his career.
</P>
<P>
   Usually by now, the Cardinals are so far out of contention,
Centers has struggled to remain motivated.
</P>
<P>
   ``There were times I wondered whether we would be able to get
things turned around here during my football lifetime,'' said
Centers, who has been with the team longer than any active player.
</P>
<P>
   Not once since Centers joined the team as a fifth-round pick in
1990 has the team been over .500 after nine games. Twice, they've
been 2-7. Five times, they've been 3-6.
</P>
<P>
   In five of those years, they've been in the division cellar.
</P>
<P>
   ``You come in and try to be the best at your profession, but it
used to be pretty hard,'' Centers said. ``It was work.
</P>
<P>
   ``The hardest thing was trying to find something to be excited
about, finding something good about the situation, something to
focus on so that it was not as bad a situation as it seemed. I
would try to go to practice and make a catch I've never made
before, make a move I never had made before.''
</P>
<P>
   The last time the Cardinals played a home game that was
televised locally, they met the Cowboys on Christmas night three
years ago on Monday Night Football.
</P>
<P>
   Before the game, ABC-TV's Dan Dierdorf walked in on middle
linebacker Eric Hill and defensive end Chad Brown brawling in the
Cardinals locker room. Then the Cardinals went out and were routed,
37-13.
</P>
<P>
   Centers wound up catching 12 passes for 172 yards and made all
of the TV highlight films when he hurdled Cowboys cornerback Larry
Brown en route to a 29-yard gain.
</P>
<P>
   He doesn't consider it one of his special moments. ``It was a
meaningless game except for the fact it was the end of a rotten
(4-12) season,'' Centers said.
</P>
<P>
   It also was the end of Coach Buddy Ryan's two-year reign of
terror. He was fired the next day.
</P>
<P>
   Centers said the attitude changed soon after Coach Vince Tobin
was hired to replace Ryan. Two years later, the Cardinals are in
contention for a division title and the NFC playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   ``Right now, we're not successful officially,'' Centers said.
``Getting where we want to get is a process. This is part of the
process.''
</P>
<P>
   After an 0-2 start, the Cardinals have won five of seven.
</P>
<P>
   ``This game is such a game of confidence,'' Centers said.
``We're starting to believe we can get it done. That's why I'm
happy the way (last Sunday's game) ended and the way we had to win
it.''
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals blew a nine-point lead in the final three minutes
last Sunday against Washington but rallied in the closing seconds
to win, 29-27, on Joe Nedney's 47-yard field goal.
</P>
<P>
   Now, whenever Centers goes out in public, fans are stopping him
and asking him about Sunday's game.
</P>
<P>
   They also want to know when the Madden cruiser arrives. The
answer is Friday.
</P>
<P>
   ``People like Larry deserve more than a game when we're 5-4 and
have a chance to share first place,'' center Aaron Graham said.
``I'm more excited about getting Larry the opportunity to play in
December for a division championship and a playoff game.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know Larry is going to be excited, because he hasn't had
this opportunity before, but I foresee bigger games down the
road.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
