<HEADLINE>
RIVALS MEET 1 LAST TIME IN COLLEGE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Ever since they were the country's most coveted high school
quarterbacks, Brock Huard and Cade McNown have impacted each
other's lives in curious ways.
</P>
<P>
   The two square off in Husky Stadium on Saturday, and McNown's
8-0 UCLA Bruins can clinch a Rose Bowl berth with the victory.
Huard's 5-4 Washington Huskies are simply trying to salvage their
season.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a funny twist of fate,'' Huard said.
</P>
<P>
   When the two were looking at colleges, McNown waited for Huard's
decision. If Huard had decided to attend UCLA, McNown would have
opted for Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Both have ridden the roller coaster.
</P>
<P>
   When the Bruins visited the Huskies two years ago and lost,
41-21, McNown met Huard on the field after the game and bemoaned
his fortune. UCLA was in the midst of a 5-6 season.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was really complaining about the play-calling and coming up
here and not having the weapons and (saying), `You have Corey
Dillon running the ball and all you do is play-action pass,' ''
Huard recalled.
</P>
<P>
   The two could face off in the NFL one day. Huard, a junior who
sat out one year as a redshirt, is expected to leave early and join
senior McNown in the draft. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Around the Pac &QL; 
 &QL; 
Huard's frustrations this season were evident Saturday to
television viewers, who saw the quarterback bark at his receivers
after drops and interceptions during a 27-22 loss to Oregon.
</P>
<P>
   At one point, the usually poised Huard actually chased Andre
DeSaussure down the field.
</P>
<P>
   He apologized to teammates the next day and later told the media
he still has confidence in his receivers.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wasn't too pleased with my vocal swearing on TV by any
means,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   It was a heart-breaking ending for Andrae Holland, out of Peoria
High School, who was an unlikely goat in Oregon State's 41-34 loss
to UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   Unlikely, because Holland is the Beavers' single-season and
career leader for passes broken up. His 15 this season leads the
Pac-10 and he also has 40 overall.
</P>
<P>
   Holland took the bait on the Bruins' final play of the game and
opted not to go deep on pass coverage. He could only watch as
UCLA's Brad Melsby took McNown's pass for the game-winning 61-yard
scoring play with 21 seconds left.
</P>
<P>
   Holland, whose reputation around the conference is that of a
class act, bravely met reporters afterward.
</P>
<P>
   ``I lost the game,'' he repeated several times, his hands over
his face. ``I blew the coverage. I was supposed to be deep and I
wasn't.''
</P>
<P>
   Melsby was not even the primary receiver on the play, ``but when
the corner bit on the 20-yard route, Cade made a great play,'' UCLA
Coach Bob Toledo said.
</P>
<P>
   Toledo let it be known this week that he's not thrilled by the
recent efforts of first-year defensive coordinator Nick Aliotti and
other assistants.
</P>
<P>
   The Bruins' struggles on defense came to a head during at Oregon
State. They allowed 34 points and 491 yards to a team that went in
averaging 23.1 and 345.9, respectively.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want them to realize that I'm not pleased with them as
well,'' Toledo said. ``And I've told them. I'm not saying anything
I haven't told them. I think we need to do a better coaching job.
It's easy to continue to blame it on the players.''
</P>
<P>
   Redshirt freshman Ken Simonton has one game and 129 yards to go
to be the first Oregon State player in nearly three decades to rush
for 1,000 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Three Pac-10 defensive backs are among 10 semifinalists for the
Jim Thorpe Award: Arizona's Chris McAlister, UCLA's Larry Atkins
and Southern California's Daylon McCutcheon. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Includes information from other media sources. Paola Boivin can be
reached at paola.boivin(at)pni.com via e-mail.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
