BANGLADESH-WATER-4, 11-11 -- Salim Uddin Mondal, father of seven,
pumps water from his tube well, despite government tests that
showed it was contaminated with arsenic. Bangladesh is in the midst
of what some experts say could be the biggest mass poisoning in
history. Dangerous levels of arsenic have been found in the ground
water, entering millions of people sip by sip as they drink from a
vast system of tube wells. Sores on this persons hand indicate
Arsenic poisoning. (Altaf Hossain/New York Times Photo)
