money from his Boston office. Having struck out on his own last
year with Kobrick Cendant Funds and Kobrick Capital Management, his
mutual fund and hedge fund firms, Kobrick is among a new breed of
independent stock-pickers staking fresh ground in the heart of
America's fund industry. (Pam Berry/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) BOSTON -- Nov. 11, 1998 -- HAITI-CONSUL-BOS, 11-11 --
Andrine Constant, the new Haitian Consul General, oversees the
packing and shipping of relief goods to be sent to Haiti in the
aftermath of Hurricane Georges. Since her appointment last month,
an onslaught of demands has kept Ms. Constant focused on the
immediate, pressing needs of Haitians at home and in Massachusetts,
which has the third-largest population of Haitians in the United
States. (Pam Berry/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
