apartment in Newark, N.J., fly across the country and down to El
Salvador, where she would frantically search for her children _
whom she has been unable to locate since a hurricane devastated
Central America two weeks ago. But Ms. Palacios can fly only in her
imagination because of a nightmarish web of federal laws and
regulations that make traveling abroad an almost impossible dream
for illegal immigrants or those in process of becoming legal
residents. By Mirta Ojito.
